07/11/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian police will take over control of the republic's borders from the army on 1 January, the interior ministry announced on Friday (5 November).
According to an official statement, the decision was made earlier in the week by Serbia-Montenegro's Supreme Defence Council.
Police initially will patrol the border with Hungary and then gradually deploy in other areas.
Montenegro's police are already patrolling the republic's own borders.
The Croatian Foreign Ministry hailed the decision to demilitarise Serbia's borders.
In other news Friday, Serbian Deputy Prime Minister Miroljub Labus proposed that an international conference on Kosovo be held in Vienna on 21 November 2005.
In an article published in the Belgrade daily <I>Politika</I>, Labus said the forum should focus on issues related to Kosovo's standards, protection of minority rights and security, decentralisation and final status.
(Tanjug, Beta, B92, Politika - 06/11/04;
AFP - 05/11/04)
